The paper proposes a scalable deep non-parametric generative model that combines deep Gaussian processes with a recognition model. The method is evaluated on deep unsupervised learning and deep Bayesian optimization tasks, indicating a focus on machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also discusses the use of multilayer perceptrons and variational frameworks, suggesting a focus on neural networks and deep learning. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The use of Gaussian processes and Bayesian optimization also suggests a potential fit with cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
